@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080

### Root / Screen
GET {{baseUrl}}/

GET {{baseUrl}}/api/screen  # alias of /

### Status
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/status

# Response example (RA as HH:MM:SS.ss, DEC as ±DD:MM:SS.ss)
```
{
  "status": "ready",
  "tracking": "sidereal",
  "ra": "12:20:42.00",
  "dec": "-32:07:12.00",
  "settings": {
    "lat": -32.890800,
    "lon": -68.827200,
    "elevation": 750
  }
}
```

### Tracking
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tracking
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tracking": "sidereal"    # one of: "none","manual","sidereal","lunar","solar"
}

### Goto
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/goto
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ra": 10.234,
  "dec": -20.123,
  "speed": 2
}

### Stop
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/stop

### Park
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/park

### Unpark
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/unpark

### Sync
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sync
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ra": 10.234,
  "dec": -20.123
}

### Move Axis
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/move-axis
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "axis": "ra",      # "ra" or "dec"
  "degrees": 15.0,
  "speed": 2
}

### Settings
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/settings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "time": "2026-05-28T10:00:00-03:00",
  "lat": -32.8908,
  "lon": -68.8272,
  "elevation": 750
}

### Command responses
All command endpoints return the standard command result JSON:
```
{"ok": true, "message": "..."}
```
On rejection the HTTP status is `409 Conflict` with `{"ok": false, "message": "reason"}`
